{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"8050128a-fe5c-473f-a9d9-6b75236cc1d4","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/round-immutable-input/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"design.md","title":"Shallow clone does not protect nested deps fields","rationale":"D2's `roundDeps = { ...deps }` is a shallow clone. Member execution that mutates a nested property (e.g. `deps.config.someField`) would still affect the shared `deps`. The Risks section correctly acknowledges this, and tests only validate `resumePrompt`/`resumeContext` immutability, which is sufficient for the stated scope. No action required for this request, but the limitation is unmentioned in spec.md Req-1."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"design.md","title":"CLI step resume note behavior not analyzed in D1","rationale":"The Pipeline `firstUnitExecuted` flag marks CLI steps as 'consumed' even though CLI steps never read `deps.resumePrompt/Context`. In the edge case where resume starts at a CLI step with a human note, old behavior propagated the note to the next agent step (since CLI did not clear deps); new behavior silently drops it. Neither is semantically correct, and the scenario is extremely unlikely in practice. The design does not mention this change."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"tasks.md","title":"T-05 migration target ambiguity — TC-RC-001~003 may be accidentally deleted","rationale":"T-05 says to 'delete/update' the in-place-clear mechanism assertions in executor-resume-context.test.ts, but does not specify that TC-RC-001~003 (resumeSessionId tests) are unaffected. An implementer reading the task could mistakenly remove all tests in those files."}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/step/executor.ts","title":"In-place clear confirmed at executor.ts:243-246","rationale":"The target mutation block (`deps.resumePrompt = undefined; deps.resumeContext = undefined;`) exists exactly where the spec describes. Design is grounded in the actual code.","line":243},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/command/resume.ts","title":"Strict equality gate confirmed at resume.ts:274","rationale":"The `startStep === resumePoint.step` gate that drops automatic context on member→coordinator resume exists exactly as described. D3 fix is correctly targeted.","line":274},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/resume/resolve-step.ts","title":"mapMemberToCoordinator is currently non-exported","rationale":"Function is declared as `function mapMemberToCoordinator` (no export keyword). T-04's export addition is the minimal correct change.","line":42}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-07-13T19:08:19.551Z","endedAt":"2026-07-13T19:14:00.216Z"}
